.TH tuck 1 "2026-02-13" "tuck" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tuck \- Modern dotfiles manager with a beautiful CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
tuck [command] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
tuck is a modern dotfiles manager that provides a beautiful CLI
for managing your configuration files across machines.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Initialize tuck
.TP
.B add
Track new dotfiles
.TP
.B remove
Stop tracking dotfiles
.TP
.B sync
Sync all dotfile changes (pull, detect, scan, track, commit, push)
.TP
.B push
Push changes to remote
.TP
.B pull
Pull changes from remote
.TP
.B restore
Restore dotfiles to the system
.TP
.B status
Show current tracking status
.TP
.B list
List all tracked files
.TP
.B diff
Show differences between system and repository
.TP
.B config
Manage tuck configuration
.TP
.B apply
Apply dotfiles from a repository to this machine, or push locally-tracked configs onto a remote box with \-\-target ssh://[user@]host (or \-\-ssh host); \-\-print\-bootstrap prints a remote install\-and\-apply one\-liner
.TP
.B bootstrap
One-command, idempotent machine setup (install packages, apply dotfiles, run doctor)
.TP
.B undo
Restore files from a Time Machine backup snapshot
.TP
.B scan
Scan the system for dotfiles and select which to track
.TP
.B secrets
Manage local secrets for placeholder replacement
.TP
.B encryption
Manage backup encryption (AES-256-GCM, password-based)
.TP
.B doctor
Run repository health and safety diagnostics
.TP
.B verify
Verify that the live system, repo, and manifest agree
.TP
.B bundle
Manage bundles \(em logical groups of tracked files
.TP
.B context
Track AI agent configs across home and per-repo scopes
.TP
.B mcp
Model Context Protocol server \(em expose tuck to AI agents
.TP
.B preset
Apply or publish curated bundles of dotfiles & agent configs
.TP
.B repo
Manage machine-local repo bindings
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show version
.SH FILES
~/.tuck
.SH SEE ALSO
git(1), stow(1)